## Required:
* Linux (test on Ubuntu 16.04)
* Install gcc 
* Install GMP 
* Install openssl (Recommend: version 1.1.x)
* Edit the makefile (the first line) to have:
	LIBS_HOME  : the directory where you have installed GMP and openssl.

## To compile:
* No optimization: make -Ibuild
* Run test : make -Ibuild run

## Test scenario of the RSA-based POR scheme (the default is 128-bit security):
* The test scenario is in the main.cpp file

## We include the built test in the default test scenario in bin. To run, use the command 'make -Ibuild run'

##Header file description:
* picosha2.h is used to implement SHA256 of generating hexadecimal hash string. Hex hash string may be directly converted to big integer type defined in GMP library. 


